news.title: Average flat sizes rose by 8% annually across seven cities in 2024: Report
news.para: The six-yearly trend of average flat sizes in the seven cities shows an overall 34% rise – from 1,145 sq ft in 2019 to 1,540 sq ft in 2024. In the last one year, there has been a 8% jump, with Hyderabad the only city to see flat sizes decrease in this period.

news.title: Retail leasing hits 6.4 million sq ft across eight cities in 2024: Report
news.para: The country added just 1.2 million sq ft of new retail space last year, but 2025 is expected to see a sharp rise in supply, with 5-6 million sq ft of grade A malls set to open in cities such as Delhi-NCR, Bengaluru, Hyderabad, and Mumbai.

news.title: New home construction in Ireland drops 6.7% to 30,000 in 2024
news.para: House completions recovered to a 15-year high of 32,500 in 2023, though that was still far below the level analysts say is needed to meet demand.

news.title: SC forms SIT to probe Noida authority's alleged irregularities in land compensation
news.para: While instances of farmers not being paid adequate compensation for land acquired by the Authority were known, it now transpires there were as many as 20 instances where complaints were lodged about payment of excess compensation to some.

news.title: Build Capital plans to invest Rs 400 crore in Mumbai region in 2025
news.para: Build Capital is targeting to invest close to Rs 150 crore in Navi Mumbai. It has made its maiden investment in Satyam Group’s project.

news.title: Kochi: GCDA seeks amendments to land pooling rules for Infopark phase III
news.para: The govt has decided to implement the project using the land pooling method, with GCDA designated as the agency to oversee the process.

news.title: MMRDA signs MoUs worth $40 billion in WEF to transform Mumbai's infra
news.para: The investments focus on urban transport, regional development and advanced technologies, promising economic growth and improved living standards in the next 3-5 years.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body recovers Rs 120 crore worth properties
news.para: The recovered property, spread over 2 acres and 16 guntas, was under illegal occupation for more than two decades.

news.title: UDH department extends construction timeline for Jaipur development body plots
news.para: Jaipur Development commissioner Anandi said that in the housing schemes of JDA, a time limit was fixed for building construction under the rules of Rajasthan Municipal Improvement Trust (Urban Land Execution) Rules 1974.

news.title: Mumbai: Residents of Kurla protest against plan to shift Dharavi tenants to Nehru Nagar
news.para: The plot, which originally belonged to Mother Dairy, was handed over to the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority (MMRDA) and subsequently transferred to the Dharavi Redevelopment Project (DRP).

news.title: Maharashtra revenue minister sets strict deadlines for Nagpur's infra projects
news.para: During a high-level meeting at Mantralaya in Mumbai on Tuesday, the minister emphasised that administrative delays would not be tolerated in the city's development agenda.

news.title: Mohali development body move to reduce enhancement charges facing delay
news.para: When Gmada allocated these plots, they secured an undertaking from the recipients to pay any future enhancement charges as determined by the authority.

news.title: Vasai Virar civic body carries out drive against illegal encroachment in Nalasopara
news.para: The demolition action has affected over 1,000 families who have been living in these buildings for several years, leaving them without homes and forcing them to face an uncertain future.

news.title: Akshay Kumar sells apartment in Mumbai for Rs 4.25 crore
news.para: Akshay Kumar had purchased the apartment in November 2017 for Rs 2.38 crore, reflecting a 78% appreciation in value in seven years.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body takes possession of two plots in Chandlodia and Thaltej
news.para: In Chandlodia, AMC took over a plot measuring 1,042 sq m reserved for a garden under TP Scheme No. 36 and a 4,462 sq m plot under TP Scheme No. 214 in Thaltej that was reserved for commercial sale.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces to jointly develop 92-acre project in Mumbai
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces' project is located near Khopoli and is signed under joint development model (70.5% revenue share). Sach Developers, are the land partners on this project.

news.title: EFC (I)'s net profit increases by 91.71% in Q3 FY25
news.para: EFC (I)'s net consolidated total income stood at Rs 181.50 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 4.50 per cent from Rs 173.68 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Infra.Market secures Rs 1,050 crore in pre-IPO funding round
news.para: The round witnessed participation from several prominent investors, including Tiger Global, Evolvence, Foundamental GmbH, Ashish Kacholia, Nikhil Kamath, Abhijit Pai, Sumeet Kanwar, Nuvama and CapriGlobal.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body to propose mandatory structural audits for highrises
news.para: Prior to this, a meeting was called by the Meerut divisional commissioner on Thursday to discuss the agenda. Sources in the GDA said that a compulsory structural audit proposal will be placed before the board.

news.title: Income tax department raids Trehan Group's properties in Alwar
news.para: Presently, the Income Tax team is executing a comprehensive search operation on-site. Nationwide, over 150 personnel from 23 teams have implemented income tax raids at 19 locations of the Trehan Group.
